1
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:07,440
Anything else you want to tell me?

2
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:10,320
A-Tai.

3
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:12,759
There's something I don't quite understand.

4
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:15,480
When you saved me earlier, you mentioned the baby.

5
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:17,239
How did you know Shen Qing was pregnant?

6
00:01:11,359 --> 00:01:13,120
Bro, bro, let's go, hurry!

7
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:19,079
Stop right there!

8
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,239
Su Zhuang!

9
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:22,439
Su Zhuang!

10
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:23,480
Bro, hurry!

11
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:24,159
The car's this way, hurry!

12
00:01:24,159 --> 00:01:24,879
Wait, wait!

13
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:33,920
Su Zhuang!

14
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,079
What happened?

15
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:36,799
Hurry!

16
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:37,959
Call an ambulance!

17
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,400
That way!

18
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,920
A man in a black trench coat, hurry!

19
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,000
After him!

20
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,200
Su Zhuang!

21
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:45,560
Su Zhuang!

22
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,040
Su Zhuang!

23
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:49,920
Su Zhuang!

24
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:08,960
Captain Wang.

25
00:02:09,599 --> 00:02:10,280
Come here, quick.

26
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,960
Were you cut by this knife?

27
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:27,960
Not this one.

28
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:30,599
The one used at Shen Qing's place

29
00:02:30,599 --> 00:02:31,479
was double-edged.

30
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,759
Both edges could inflict damage.

31
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,319
It looked like a military dagger.

32
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:37,039
About 20 centimeters long,

33
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:38,520
with an extremely sharp blade.

34
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,639
But this one

35
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:42,120
looks more like a household fruit knife.

36
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,159
Run blood tests and lift fingerprints right away.

37
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,240
Got it.

38
00:02:59,439 --> 00:03:00,039
Li Kaiyang.

39
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,840
Why did you take the suspect away on your own?

40
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,159
Who gave you the nerve?

41
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,000
Now Su Zhuang is dead.

42
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,800
How am I supposed to answer to my superiors?

43
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,919
How are we supposed to crack this case?

44
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,439
Li Kaiyang.

45
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,439
I warned you.

46
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:12,639
Don't act recklessly.

47
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:14,280
Why didn't you listen?

48
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,240
Now look what's happened.

49
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:18,400
The leads on the case are gone.

50
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:21,039
All our past efforts have gone to waste.

51
00:03:21,879 --> 00:03:23,000
Tell me, what do we do now?

52
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:24,759
I will absolutely not shirk my responsibility.

53
00:03:25,719 --> 00:03:27,639
I just think this whole thing is suspicious.

54
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,560
The moment I took Su Zhuang out of the hospital,

55
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,919
the killer showed up at Shen Qing's villa.

56
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,360
Do you think that's normal?

57
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:36,680
What are you implying?

58
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,719
Are you suspecting there's a leak inside?

59
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,319
Li Kaiyang.

60
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,759
Stop making excuses for your reckless actions.

61
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,759
It's all my fault.

62
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,919
I haven't been strict enough with you.

63
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:49,159
That's why you've stirred up such a huge mess.

64
00:03:49,759 --> 00:03:51,599
From the moment we moved on Ma Shijiang,

65
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:53,800
we cast a wide net.

66
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,800
And he still got away.

67
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:59,240
My mentor Zhao Qingming died under murky circumstances.

68
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,919
With his skill, killed by some petty thug?

69
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,000
Do you think that's normal?

70
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,919
So you're saying it's my fault?

71
00:04:13,439 --> 00:04:15,159
Didn't I give you the authority to investigate?

72
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:17,319
Did you find anything?

73
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,879
I'm not blaming anyone.

74
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:22,120
When we were interrogating Su Zhuang,

75
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,439
if he hadn't suddenly collapsed,

76
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,680
he would have confessed everything.

77
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,480
But when he woke up,

78
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:29,680
he suddenly backed out and refused to say a word.

79
00:04:30,079 --> 00:04:31,439
Do you think that's normal?

80
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,240
Why are you looking at me like that?

81
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,120
Don't tell me you suspect me.

82
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,120
After Su Zhuang woke up,

83
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,560
you were the only one to visit his room alone.

84
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,879
Li Kaiyang!

85
00:04:44,759 --> 00:04:46,199
I've put up with you long enough.

86
00:04:46,759 --> 00:04:48,480
I don't care if you disrespect me,

87
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,600
but suspecting me of colluding with criminals?

88
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,800
That, I absolutely will not tolerate.

89
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:53,839
Where's your evidence?

90
00:04:55,199 --> 00:04:55,800
Enough!

91
00:04:57,079 --> 00:04:58,560
Look at the two of you.

92
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,959
Squabbling like defeated roosters in your own coop.

93
00:05:04,279 --> 00:05:05,000
Li Kaiyang,

94
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:07,199
if you suspected an internal problem,

95
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,680
why didn't you come to me?

96
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,040
Do you even respect the chain of command?

97
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,160
I...

98
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,040
"I" what?

99
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,759
Your recklessness

100
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,319
led directly to the suspect's death.

101
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:18,879
Have you thought about the consequences?

102
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,040
You claim Su Zhuang was murdered.

103
00:05:21,879 --> 00:05:22,680
Who can prove it?

104
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,720
You claim there was a killer in a trench coat in the woods.

105
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:28,040
So many officers searched for hours

106
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,639
and didn't find a single trace.

107
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,199
How do you explain that?

108
00:05:31,639 --> 00:05:33,720
I did all this just to solve the case.

109
00:05:34,759 --> 00:05:36,920
Enough. Talking to you is a waste of breath.

110
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:40,600
You haven't even realized your own mistakes.

111
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:42,079
Li Kaiyang,

112
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:43,560
I know

113
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:46,439
you've cracked many major cases.

114
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,639
But the Major Crimes Unit

115
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,079
doesn't belong to you alone.

116
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,839
You still have a captain above you.

117
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:54,519
Acting on your own without reporting,

118
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,480
causing such serious consequences,

119
00:05:57,319 --> 00:05:58,600
is enough to destroy all the honor

120
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,879
this force has built up over the years.

121
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:02,839
Can't you even reflect on your own actions?

122
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:04,600
Li Kaiyang,

123
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:07,839
is admitting you were wrong really so hard?

124
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,720
Debating right and wrong here is pointless.

125
00:06:10,639 --> 00:06:12,959
All I know is I need to solve this case fast.

126
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:15,519
Give me one week.

127
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,160
I'll definitely give you an answer.

128
00:06:17,439 --> 00:06:18,160
No need.

129
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,639
Given your serious breach of discipline,

130
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,279
acting on your own,

131
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:25,560
and causing irreversible consequences,

132
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:26,600
as of now,

133
00:06:26,879 --> 00:06:27,680
you're suspended pending review.

134
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:28,920
Captain Xing...

135
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:29,759
Don't say another word.

136
00:06:29,959 --> 00:06:31,800
Go back and write a thorough self-criticism.

137
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:34,639
And you, for poor handling of the case,

138
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,439
go back and submit a written review.

139
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,360
Master.

140
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:54,879
Master.

141
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:56,800
Are you alright?

142
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:58,759
I heard you've been suspended.

143
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:01,120
I'll go talk to Captain Xing.

144
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:01,800
Get back here.

145
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,600
Captain Xing's decision follows protocol.

146
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,319
What are you trying to do?

147
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:07,560
Didn't Captain Xing approve your trip?

148
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,079
The one who stabbed Lin Xiaohu...

149
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,399
has a viper tattoo on his arm.

150
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:14,040
Right?

151
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,600
Yeah.

152
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,319
He must be the one who killed Su Zhuang too.

153
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:18,680
And this guy...

154
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:20,160
was close to Su Zhuang.

155
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Otherwise, Su Zhuang wouldn't have flipped at the last minute.

156
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:26,199
But that still doesn't add up.

157
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:28,240
He went through all that trouble to rescue Su Zhuang,

158
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,360
just to kill him in the woods?

159
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,519
What kind of move is that?

160
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,680
That proves there's someone else pulling the strings.

161
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,680
He's getting nervous.

162
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,560
Silencing witnesses now.

163
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,399
How did he know you went to Shen Qing's place?

164
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,920
You only mentioned it in the hospital room.

165
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:43,920
Does he have super hearing?

166
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,519
Why are you looking at me like that?

167
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,600
Super hearing...

168
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,160
Why didn't I think of that?

169
00:07:58,079 --> 00:07:58,600
Hey.

170
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,759
What are you touching?

171
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:11,519
I just mopped. I need to change the sheets.

172
00:08:14,879 --> 00:08:15,439
Get out.

173
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:21,600
Master.

174
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,360
What's wrong?

175
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,160
When Su Zhuang was sick,

176
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:31,439
he was very weak.

177
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,759
His voice was very faint.

178
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:38,639
You suspect there's a bug in here?

179
00:08:48,519 --> 00:08:50,919
Because I only mentioned it in this room,

180
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,360
that I'd take Su Zhuang to see Shen Qing's gift.

181
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,919
The killer can't have super hearing.

182
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,080
Or else...

183
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,360
you're the one who told the killer.

184
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,120
No.

185
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:09,159
Master.

186
00:09:09,559 --> 00:09:09,960
I...

187
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,679
"I" what?

188
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:12,039
It wasn't you.

189
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:12,759
"You" what?

190
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,720
Next time you have such a brilliant idea,

191
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,559
could you tell me a little sooner?

192
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,080
Master, you scared me to death.

193
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,279
Could you give me a heads-up next time you joke around?

194
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,840
But there's something I can't figure out.

195
00:09:28,679 --> 00:09:29,879
When the killer knocked me out,

196
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,200
he had every chance to kill Su Zhuang.

197
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,480
So why didn't he?

198
00:09:34,559 --> 00:09:35,240
Exactly.

199
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,759
Why would they go through all that trouble?

200
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:37,679
Something's off here.

201
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,240
And it's a really big problem.

202
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:41,919
Master.

203
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,960
You don't suspect someone on the inside...

204
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,639
Shut your mouth.

205
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:52,080
Let's talk somewhere else.

206
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:57,759
Master.

207
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:01,039
You suspect someone planted a bug?

208
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,240
In all my years on the force,

209
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,639
I've rarely felt this lost on a case.

210
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:11,960
It's like being adrift in a vast ocean,

211
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,519
with nothing to grab onto.

212
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,879
If even you're lost,

213
00:10:18,279 --> 00:10:19,639
then I'm even more lost.

214
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,279
Do you really suspect there's a mole inside?

215
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,240
Who do you suspect?

216
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,480
When Su Zhuang was in there,

217
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,240
every single person who entered that room

218
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,240
is a suspect.

219
00:10:33,519 --> 00:10:34,840
That's a huge suspect pool, then.

220
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,399
Not just our people.

221
00:10:36,879 --> 00:10:38,279
Doctors, nurses,

222
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,799
even the cleaning staff.

223
00:10:40,879 --> 00:10:42,600
Our people were watching all of them.

224
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:45,919
So the problem lies with one of our own.

225
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:52,919
You...

226
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,320
You don't suspect Captain Wang, do you?

227
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,840
What do you think?

228
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,039
I don't dare to think about it.

229
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,440
Before I joined the police force,

230
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,639
I prepared myself mentally for a lot.

231
00:11:13,159 --> 00:11:14,840
But I never imagined the cases I'd face

232
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,039
would be way bigger than I thought.

233
00:11:20,519 --> 00:11:21,600
Can I trust you,

234
00:11:22,879 --> 00:11:23,480
Master?

235
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,679
That's a bit insulting, isn't it?

236
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:26,679
I mean,

237
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,440
From the day I, Jiang Han, joined the CID,

238
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:31,200
I swore an oath,

239
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,840
I'd rather lay down my life

240
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,080
than dishonor the badge I wear.

241
00:11:35,799 --> 00:11:37,440
Besides, don't you know what kind of person I am?

242
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,440
I...

243
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,519
Whatever you ask me to do, I...

244
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:40,440
I can feel it.

245
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,200
Back when I was on the force,

246
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,000
the one I trusted most was Captain Zhao.

247
00:11:48,799 --> 00:11:49,600
Now it's you.

248
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:55,279
Master,

249
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,320
what are you really trying to say?

250
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,080
You and Captain Xing,

251
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,080
are you close?

252
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:09,679
Somewhat.

253
00:12:11,639 --> 00:12:13,120
My dad used to be his superior.

254
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:15,440
But after my dad retired,

255
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:17,720
we lost touch.

256
00:12:19,519 --> 00:12:20,799
Then how well do you know Xing Mingliang?

257
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:22,799
Even less so.

258
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,720
Met him when I was a kid,

259
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:26,200
shared a few meals.

260
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,240
But no personal contact at all.

261
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,919
So what's your take on him?

262
00:12:34,519 --> 00:12:36,759
Him? I think his personality is a bit strange.

263
00:12:37,639 --> 00:12:39,279
Gives off a "keep your distance" vibe.

264
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,759
You don't suspect Xing Mingliang, do you?

265
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:49,080
Same as you,

266
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,639
I think it's strange too.

267
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:52,919
He just shows up out of nowhere

268
00:12:52,919 --> 00:12:54,159
and beats Meng Yu into a vegetative state.

269
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:57,720
Something's definitely off about it.

270
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,240
Mingliang loves Ruolan so deeply,

271
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,120
and Meng Yu tried to assault her.

272
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:05,120
He confronts Meng Yu in anger,

273
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,320
Meng Yu tries to silence him,

274
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:08,320
he fights back and puts him in a coma.

275
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,279
The logic checks out.

276
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:10,159
The logic works,

277
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,720
but there are no witnesses left.

278
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:15,320
Ever since the Red Glove appeared,

279
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:17,360
there's been so much that doesn't add up.

280
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:18,960
In the case of Shen Qing's fall,

281
00:13:19,919 --> 00:13:22,039
several times we were on the verge of the truth.

282
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:23,279
But...

283
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,240
the leads just vanished like smoke,

284
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,320
disappearing without a trace.

285
00:13:29,879 --> 00:13:31,919
As if controlled by an invisible hand,

286
00:13:34,039 --> 00:13:35,360
pushing us deeper

287
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:37,759
into more tangled mysteries.

288
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,039
Who do you think sent the killer?

289
00:13:45,639 --> 00:13:46,840
That's exactly the problem.

290
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,480
Logically, whoever tried to kill Lin Xiaohu

291
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,679
should've been sent by Su Zhuang.

292
00:13:53,039 --> 00:13:54,799
But this same person saved Su Zhuang,

293
00:13:55,919 --> 00:13:57,360
and then turned around and killed him.

294
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:08,200
I feel like I'm standing on the edge of a cliff.

295
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,159
Looking down,

296
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,279
it's a bottomless abyss.

297
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,639
Looking up,

298
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,320
and that invisible hand looms over me.

299
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,200
I can't see any light.

300
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:25,840
Jiang Han,

301
00:14:30,039 --> 00:14:31,480
if we keep moving forward,

302
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,519
we could be torn to pieces.

303
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,799
Are you still willing to walk this path with me?

304
00:14:39,919 --> 00:14:40,639
Master,

305
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,600
you're really underestimating me.

306
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,879
Am I, Jiang Han, the type to fear death?

307
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,000
Even if I fall into the deepest abyss,

308
00:14:47,399 --> 00:14:49,000
I'll uncover the truth with you.

309
00:14:49,279 --> 00:14:51,519
Even if that dark hand crushes me to pieces,

310
00:14:52,279 --> 00:14:53,679
I'll risk my life fighting back.

311
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,639
It's time to go back to the beginning.

312
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,120
Shen Qing, Ma Shijiang,

313
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,639
what was the connection between them?

314
00:15:14,559 --> 00:15:15,480
That club,

315
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,000
and Ma Shijiang's disappearance,

316
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,559
what's the link between them?

317
00:15:21,679 --> 00:15:23,799
And the cabin Su Zhuang mentioned before he died,

318
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,320
what did that even mean?

319
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,480
The cabin...

320
00:15:33,759 --> 00:15:35,240
He also gave me a key.

321
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:36,919
Su Zhuang!

322
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,279
Captain Li...

323
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:46,759
Go...

324
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,200
Go to...

325
00:15:49,039 --> 00:15:49,799
the...

326
00:15:50,759 --> 00:15:51,440
cabin.

327
00:16:08,639 --> 00:16:09,480
What are you doing?

328
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,039
Who told you to let Xing Mingliang go?

329
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,519
What's wrong with you?

330
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,960
You're nowhere to be found all day.

331
00:16:16,039 --> 00:16:17,200
How was I supposed to let you know?

332
00:16:17,799 --> 00:16:18,919
Xing Mingliang's actions

333
00:16:18,919 --> 00:16:21,600
meet the criteria for self-defense.

334
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,159
He asked to recover at home.

335
00:16:23,559 --> 00:16:24,399
Could I refuse?

336
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,759
Besides, Captain Xing approved it.

337
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,480
Meng Yu is still in a coma.

338
00:16:28,919 --> 00:16:30,720
Have you confirmed what really happened?

339
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,159
Then what do you suggest?

340
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,440
Lock Xing Mingliang up?

341
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:35,679
Wait for Meng Yu to wake up?

342
00:16:36,519 --> 00:16:37,799
What if he never wakes up?

343
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,600
Every "truth" we know right now

344
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,240
is just Xing Mingliang's one-sided story.

345
00:16:41,519 --> 00:16:42,480
Let me remind you,

346
00:16:42,759 --> 00:16:44,000
don't suck up to your superiors

347
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,480
and forget your actual duty.

348
00:16:45,679 --> 00:16:46,440
Li Kaiyang!

349
00:16:46,799 --> 00:16:47,759
Don't push it.

350
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:49,519
I'm the captain here.

351
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:50,960
I know exactly what to do.

352
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,240
I really hope you do.

353
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,360
I don't need you lecturing me.

354
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,080
Master, something big happened.

355
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:55,559
What is it?

356
00:16:55,559 --> 00:16:56,159
Come on, let's go.

357
00:16:56,799 --> 00:16:57,320
Go.

358
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,240
My fingerprints?

359
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,440
That's impossible.

360
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:03,679
I couldn't believe it either.

361
00:17:03,679 --> 00:17:05,160
But I checked it over and over.

362
00:17:05,559 --> 00:17:06,200
In a little while,

363
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:08,200
I have to report the results to Captain Wang.

364
00:17:08,759 --> 00:17:10,599
Captain Li, tell me the truth.

365
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,759
Did you have anything to do with Su Zhuang's death?

366
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,039
Fei, you actually suspect my master?

367
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,559
I'm stating the facts.

368
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:18,400
Master,

369
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,119
didn't you say you never touched that knife?

370
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:21,480
Then why are your prints on it?

371
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,200
I can guarantee,

372
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,839
once that knife arrived at forensics,

373
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:26,359
no one touched it.

374
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:28,480
I lifted the prints right away.

375
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,839
Who delivered the knife?

376
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,039
Lin Xue.

377
00:17:33,519 --> 00:17:34,119
I'll go find her.

378
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:34,759
Get back here!

379
00:17:35,759 --> 00:17:37,640
I'm the only witness to Su Zhuang's death.

380
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,519
I can't explain it.

381
00:17:40,079 --> 00:17:41,039
Then what do we do?

382
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:42,200
Fei,

383
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,200
keep the fingerprint report quiet for me.

384
00:17:45,599 --> 00:17:46,960
I can't sit on this!

385
00:17:58,880 --> 00:17:59,440
Hello?

386
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:00,759
Dad?

387
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:02,000
What did you say?
